<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2008/10/01/dear-apologists-for-immoral-and-unconstitutional-laws/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Dear Apologists for Immoral and Unconstitutional Laws">Dear Apologists for Immoral and Unconstitutional Laws</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>Can you believe that lady? High ideals are all well and good, but she knew the rules. So unprofessional! She didn&#8217;t have to take that bus. If you don&#8217;t like the rules, don&#8217;t ride the bus. I&#8217;m an industry professional, and I give up my seat all the time &#8211; that&#8217;s what &#8220;professional&#8221; means. What if it were YOUR bus? You certainly wouldn&#8217;t want just any riff-raff riding it as they pleased. Plus if she&#8217;s so great, she should have raised $220,000 for skin-lightening cream &#8211; problem solved. Or buy her own bus! But no, she thinks she&#8217;s so special. What a whiner.</p>
</p>
<p>Too bad people forget the story of Rosa Parks
